Kalmar RK-krets sed. 20, ordf. sed. 46, led. av styr. f. Riksfören. f. svenskh. bev. i uti. o. Moderata kvin-nokl. GMmf, SMsjv.
translated: Engdahl, Elsa Olena Mathilda, former principal, Gösisäter, born on June 20th, 1881 in Kalmar to physician Edvard E. and Bertha Andersson. She graduated from the teacher training program in Stockholm in 1902, specializing in the fourth department in 1906. She worked as a substitute teacher at Kalmar elementary school and others from 1902 to 1903, and as a subject teacher in the same school from 1903 to 1936, serving as its chairman from 1925 to 1936. She was the principal of the Kalmar municipal girls' school from 1936 to 1946. She was a member of the Stockholm city council from 1923 to 1925, and a member of the board for the Kalmar Red Cross district since 1920. She was elected as a chairman in 1946. She was a member of the board for the Swedish Society for Race Hygiene Abroad and the Moderate Women's Club. She married but her partner's name is not provided.
